# English code, localized user copy

See the same convention as the TourAI monorepo: internal code in English; Spanish only for user-visible web copy and `es-ES` i18n strings.

- **English:** script names, CSS classes used by layout code, JS identifiers, `scripts/*.js`, export tooling, commit messages.
- **Spanish allowed:** HTML body text on Spanish pages, `page.*` content in default HTML, Spanish sidebar/help copy meant for end users.
- **Not Spanish:** script names, module paths, and internal tooling filenames; Spanish only in user-facing document bodies when the audience is Spanish-speaking.
